SC,0008
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F345A1667777620
OL,5,FOn Thursday afternoon, the BBC News at
OL,6,FOne gained a far bigger audience than
OL,7,Fnormal as speculation Liz Truss was
OL,8,Fabout to quit grew. It began with 3m
OL,9,Fand peaked as she spoke, at around
OL,10,F1.30pm.
OL,12,FThe ITV Lunchtime News only registered
OL,13,Fa slight rise in ratings.
OL,15,FLater, the News at Six scored above 5m
OL,16,Ffor the first time for several weeks 
OL,17,Fthe ITV Evening News, again, had its
OL,18,Fnormal audience of around 3m.
OL,3,CWhy BBC News can't do Bradby-style
OL,4,Cintros
OL,22,                                  G8/10
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34509
SC,0009
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F345A1667777620
OL,5,FAnd if you wanted a late-evening round
OL,6,Fup, ITV News at Ten was  yet again 
OL,7,FNews at When. It went on the air
OL,8,Fshortly after 10.10pm  scheduled after
OL,9,Fan extended edition of DNA Journey.
OL,11,FNo prizes for guessing which news
OL,12,Fprogramme had, by far, the bigger
OL,13,Faudience.
OL,15,FThere is no bigger test of trust for
OL,16,Fthe BBC than how it reports on an
OL,17,Fongoing political crisis.
OL,3,CWhy BBC News can't do Bradby-style
OL,4,Cintros
OL,22,                                  G9/10
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S      G
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34510
SC,0010
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F345A1667777620
OL,5,FIt needs to be more than simply fair
OL,6,Fand accurate. Getting the tone wrong in
OL,7,Fany sense on an occasion like this can
OL,8,Fhave huge consequences.
OL,3,CWhy BBC News can't do Bradby-style
OL,4,Cintros
